The paper deals with unsupervised learning in computer vision, specifically in the context of segmenting foreground objects in images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel system for unsupervised learning, which involves training multiple students with different deep network architectures, and using an automatic selection module to pick good frame segmentations. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also mentions experiments on datasets for object discovery in video, unsupervised image segmentation, and saliency detection, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) categories as well.
